<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06360070 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06360070 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  A militant black group that is boycotting power-sharing talks with thegovernment claimed responsibility Tuesday for a drive-by shooting in Soweto,South Africa, that killed one policeman and injured another. It was the secondtime in two weeks that the Pan Africanist Congress said it had attackedpolicemen in black townships near Johannesburg. The group boycotted lastweek's start of negotiations on ending white minority rule, saying the talkswere a government ploy to extend white rule.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MILITANT GROUP KILLS SOWETO POLICEMAN  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Foreign News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911225  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  December  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  83  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, December 25, 199100360070,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>